title: Kendall Jenner Sports Pink Hair While Introducing CFDA/Vogue Fashion Fund Finalists
text:
Comments The 'Keeping Up with the Kardashians' star dyed her hair pink while introducing Gypsy Sport's designer Rio Uribe, one of 10 CFDA/Vogue Fashion Fund. 
Kendall Jenner dyed her hair pink while she introduced one of 10 CFDA/Vogue Fashion Fund finalists in the November issue of Vogue magazine. The 19-year-old model also got a little help from her friends including Jaden Smith , Nick Jonas and Gigi Hadid . In a picture where the " Keeping Up with the Kardashians " star introduced Gypsy Sport's designer Rio Uribe, she donned metallic crop top and bright trousers. Jaden was pictured jumping in front of TV sets as the designer was sitting on a pile of the TV sets. Foto kiriman Vogue (@voguemagazine) pada Okt 20, 2015 pada 10:15 PDT Another snap saw Kendall as a soldier alongside Nick. Kendall wore a white military-style jumpsuit and a headpiece. For this snap, Kendall went back with her natural raven hair. Nick who appeared next to her wore a World War II-inspired outfit from the the military-influenced brand Cadet. Foto kiriman Vogue (@voguemagazine) pada Okt 20, 2015 pada 2:18 PDT Gigi posted on Instagram on Tuesday, October 20 a picture of her alongside Kendall to introduce designer Jonathan Simkhai. The two looked feminine in the black-and-white picture. Kendall wore white frock while Gigi wore the black one. Gigi captioned it, "Wearing @jonathansimkhai while dancing to Michael Buble 's Christmas album with da bestie makes me happy... clearly. @VOGUEMAGAZINE." Foto kiriman Gigi Hadid (@gigihadid) pada Okt 20, 2015 pada 8:06 PDT Designers of Thaddeus O'Neil, CG, Brother Vellies, Chromat, David Hart, Baja East and Baldwin are the other finalists for this year's CFDA/Vogue Fashion Fund. In addition to a mentorship by prominent designers and industry executives, the winner will receive a cash prize of $400,000 while two runner-ups will receive $150,000 each.
